@page "/item/{Id:int}"

@* THE INSTANCE-REUSE WITNESS, and the reason this page carries state it does not otherwise need.

   Blazor does NOT re-create a component when only its route parameters changed: navigating /item/7 ->
   /item/8 reuses the instance, so #seen keeps whatever it was bumped to and OnInitialized does not run
   again. Only #id changes. A router that re-mounts unconditionally shows #seen back at 0, which is the
   divergence the honesty register measured (n=3 -> n=0) and decision 163 closes. *@
<div id="page"><h2 id="where">item</h2><span id="id">@Id</span><span id="seen">@seen</span><button id="bump" @onclick="Bump">bump</button><a id="to-8" href="/item/8">8</a><a id="to-home" href="/">home</a></div>

@code {
    [Parameter] public int Id { get; set; }

    private int seen = 0;

    private void Bump()
    {
        seen++;
    }
}
